"jsonContent":{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s6",
"title":{
"__html":"Peptic Ulcer Disease"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"9b8acc",
"children":[
"Peptic Ulcer Disease"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s6_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a641f7",
"children":[
"Most ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"peptic ulcer disease",
"children":[
"PUD"
]
},
" is caused by ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Helicobacter pylori"
]
},
" infection or use of ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"eca42e",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"All patients with PUD should be tested for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" infection regardless of NSAID use."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"57d2af",
"children":[
"Complications of PUD:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"88fca9",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Penetration"
]
},
" is characterized by a gradual increase in the severity and frequency of abdominal pain, with acute pancreatitis as a common presentation."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2041b0",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Perforation"
]
},
" is characterized by severe, sudden abdominal pain that is often associated with shock and peritoneal signs."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0ab8a2",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Outlet obstruction"
]
},
" is characterized by nausea, vomiting, and/or early satiety and a succussion splash."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4a8ef3",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Bleeding"
]
},
" is characterized by hematemesis, melena, or hematochezia (see Upper ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"gastrointestinal",
"children":[
"GI"
]
},
" Bleeding)."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s6_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"53ad88",
"children":[
"PUD is most often diagnosed by upper endoscopy. Diagnostic tests for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" should be obtained. Options include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3334a5",
"children":[
"gastric biopsies during upper endoscopy"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"15ffb2",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"13"
]
},
"C-urea breath test"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c37073",
"children":[
"stool antigen test"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"95c059",
"children":[
"serologic testing (",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay",
"children":[
"ELISA"
]
},
" for IgG antibodies)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"421655",
"children":[
"Negative testing for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" completed in the acute setting should be repeated after discharge."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fe62af",
"children":[
"False-negative rapid urease tests, urea breath tests, and stool antigen results for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" may occur in patients who recently took antibiotics, bismuth-containing compounds, or ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"proton pump inhibitor",
"children":[
"PPI"
]
},
"s;"
]
},
" these drugs should be stopped before testing (28 days for antibiotics, 2 weeks for PPIs) or histologic assessment for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" is performed."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ad74d5",
"children":[
"Serum antibody testing for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" will not differentiate between past and current infection; a negative test excludes infection, but a positive test cannot confirm current infection."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"333ac0",
"children":[
"Duodenal ulcers carry little risk for malignancy and do not require biopsy unless they are refractory to therapy."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s6_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"010e4c",
"children":[
"For uncomplicated PUD, begin once-daily PPI and stop any aspirin or NSAIDs. Treat ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" if present."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gi_s6_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"cdc4b3",
"children":[
"Initial ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" therapy should be based on assessment of the probability of high resistance rates to clarithromycin (previous treatment with a macrolide, local resistance rates ≥15%, or eradication rates with clarithromycin-based triple therapy <85%)."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0d7a9a",
"children":[
"If resistance to clarithromycin is unlikely, use clarithromycin-based triple therapy."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"94a811",
"children":[
"If resistance to clarithromycin is probable, use bismuth quadruple therapy."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7121cf",
"children":[
"When first-line therapy fails, a salvage regimen (administered for at least 14 days) should avoid previously used antibiotics."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s6_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Follow-up"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b9c20d",
"children":[
"Follow-up"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2a38c2",
"children":[
"Follow-up noninvasive testing to document ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" eradication should be performed 4 weeks after completion of therapy by using a ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"13"
]
},
"C-urea breath test, fecal antigen test, or gastric biopsy."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"104f13",
"children":[
"Follow-up upper endoscopy for gastric ulcers is indicated if biopsies were not performed during initial upper endoscopy."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"543112",
"children":[
"Duodenal PUD without complications does not require follow-up upper endoscopy."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"baf353",
"children":[
"Serologic testing should not be used to confirm ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
" eradication, because results may remain positive in the absence of active infection."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s6_5",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"72e8da",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 42-year-old man was treated with a PPI, amoxicillin, and clarithromycin for an ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"H. pylori"
]
},
"–positive duodenal ulcer. He returns 9 weeks after treatment because of recurrent symptoms."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"710380",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For management, select urea breath test. If positive, re-treat with antibiotics different from those prescribed initially for at least 14 days."
]
}
]
}
]
},
